
# 🎬 Movie Ratings Analysis Using NumPy, Pandas & Matplotlib

A complete exploratory data analysis (EDA) project that analyzes movie ratings, budgets, and revenues using **NumPy**, **Pandas**, and **Matplotlib**. The project demonstrates data cleaning, statistical analysis, grouping operations, and data visualization to uncover insights from a movie dataset.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project performs an end-to-end analysis of a movie dataset by:

* Loading data from a GitHub-hosted CSV file
* Cleaning and preprocessing the dataset
* Performing statistical analysis using NumPy
* Analyzing movies by genre, director, and release year
* Creating insightful visualizations with Matplotlib
* Identifying the highest-rated and highest-grossing movies

This project is ideal for beginners learning **Python for Data Analysis** and **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)**.

---

## 🚀 Features

* ✅ Data Loading from GitHub
* ✅ Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
* ✅ Missing Value Handling
* ✅ Duplicate Removal
* ✅ Statistical Analysis using NumPy
* ✅ GroupBy Analysis using Pandas
* ✅ Data Visualization using Matplotlib
* ✅ Movie Insights and Summary Statistics

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

* Python 3
