---

## 📊 Dataset

The dataset contains movie-related information such as:

| Column   | Description        |
| -------- | ------------------ |
| Movie    | Movie Title        |
| Genre    | Movie Genre        |
| Director | Director Name      |
| Year     | Release Year       |
| Rating   | IMDb/User Rating   |
| Budget   | Movie Budget       |
| Revenue  | Box Office Revenue |

---

## ⚙️ Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Movie-Ratings-Analysis.git
```

Move into the project directory:

```bash
cd Movie-Ratings-Analysis
```

Install the required libraries:

```bash
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib
```

---

## ▶️ Running the Project

Launch Jupyter Notebook:

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

Open:

```text
Movie_Ratings_Analysis_Using_NumPy,_Pandas,_and_Matplotlib.ipynb
```

Run all cells to reproduce the complete analysis.

---

## 📈 Analysis Performed

### Data Exploration

* Display first rows
* Dataset dimensions
* Column information
* Data types
* Missing value analysis

### Data Cleaning

* Remove duplicate records
* Convert numeric columns
* Handle missing values

### Statistical Analysis

* Mean Rating
* Median Rating
* Standard Deviation
* Minimum Rating
* Maximum Rating

### Grouped Analysis

* Average Rating by Genre
* Average Rating by Director
* Average Rating by Release Year

---

## 📉 Visualizations

The notebook generates several visualizations:

* 📊 Average Rating by Genre (Bar Chart)
* 📊 Average Rating by Director (Bar Chart)
* 📈 Average Ratings Over Years (Line Chart)
* 🔵 Budget vs Rating (Scatter Plot)
* 🔵 Revenue vs Rating (Scatter Plot)
* 🏆 Top 10 Highest Rated Movies (Horizontal Bar Chart)

